## Workflow

### Step 1: Code Development

The developer creates or modifies application code and pushes changes to the GitHub repository.

### Step 2: GitHub Webhook Trigger

A GitHub webhook automatically sends a notification to Jenkins whenever new code is pushed to the repository.

### Step 3: Jenkins Pipeline Execution

Jenkins receives the webhook request and starts the CI/CD pipeline automatically.

### Step 4: Source Code Checkout

Jenkins clones the latest source code from the GitHub repository.

### Step 5: Docker Image Build

Jenkins executes the Docker build command:

```bash
docker build -t cicd-app:latest .
```

A new Docker image is created from the Dockerfile.

### Step 6: Container Deployment

Jenkins stops and removes the existing container (if present) and deploys a new container using the latest image.

```bash
docker stop cicd-container || true
docker rm cicd-container || true
docker run -d -p 80:80 --name cicd-container cicd-app:latest
```

### Step 7: Application Access

The application becomes available through the AWS EC2 Public IP on port 80.

```text
http://EC2-PUBLIC-IP
```

